<subSubSection pageId="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,582,1219]" box="[151,636,582,607]" pageId="6">
Length. Male: 
<quantity box="[317,447,582,607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="2.2" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.9">1.9–2.5mm</quantity>
; female: 
<quantity box="[550,632,583,607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,582,1219]" pageId="6">
Greenish ochraceous (Plate 
<collectionCode box="[514,537,619,642]" pageId="6">II</collectionCode>
: A). Head broader than pronotum. Vertex centrally with black marking between anterior margins of eyes. Two black spots at posterior margin of vertex. Pronotum shiny, with black spots, laterally carinate. Scutellum dark brown with posterior margin yellowish. Ocelli at anterior margin (Plate 
<collectionCode box="[1358,1381,691,714]" pageId="6">II</collectionCode>
: B). Frontoclypeus entirely black, anteclypeus black with yellow lateral margin (Plate 
<collectionCode box="[1087,1110,727,750]" pageId="6">II</collectionCode>
: D). Forewing macropterous with brown veins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,582,1219]" pageId="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,798,823]" pageId="6">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with darkly sclerotized part on posteroventral margin more than its half, with sparse spinules, dorsoapical margin With 2–3 macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[730,829,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: A). Spinular dark serration present in a row near anal tube base. Connective Y-shaped with arms wide apart from each other (
<figureCitation box="[980,1082,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: C). Subgenital plate with 3–4 macrosetae, smaller than pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[555,658,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: B). Style with well developed claw-like apophysis, inner process longer than outer process, wide apart (
<figureCitation box="[579,678,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: D). Aedeagal shaft gently curved dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1172,1271,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: E–F).
</paragraph>
